column18: 02/25/2003: At 2:00AM local time, a bomb exploded near the Spanish Embassy in Caracas' La Castellana neighborhood. There was some structural damage to the Embassy, and surrounding cars were damaged as well. Leaflets supporting a group called the Bolivarian Liberation Force/Simon Bolivar Coordinating Committee, a known radical pro-Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez group, were found on the street in front of the Embassy. The Police Director for the Chacao District of Caracas believed that C-4 explosives were used in the attack. Chavez announced on 02/28/2003 that the Venezuelan Government had identified suspects in the attack.

column18: 7/30/1999: A small commercial plane carrying 16 people was hijacked while traveling between Barinas and Guasdualito in Venezuela.   The passengers were released from the custody of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) on August 9, 1999.  FARC denies responsibility for the kidnapping; they claim that three hijackers fled after landing the plane in Colombia.  FARC claims that opponents of Venezuela's president are responsible for the hijacking.
